he was also a member of the harvard law review and a sheldon fellow while at or shortly after his time at harvard he traveled to cairo egypt to study islamic legal jurisprudence and law and became proficient in various islamic legal cliques developing a nearnative fluency in modern standard arabic later bonderman developed the bonderman fellows program at the university of washington providing undergraduate and graduate students with opportunities for unstructured international travel and study career historyedit bonderman was an assistant professor at tulane university law school during  and  he then was a special assistant to the united states attorney general during  and  in  he joined the law firm of arnold  porter in washington dc where he became a partner and specialized in corporate securities bankruptcy and antitrust litigation in  he joined the robert m bass group inc rmbg which now does business as keystone inc and become the chief operating officer bonderman has been a principal at tpg capital in fort worth texas since december  where he is also cofounder and chairman in  bonderman was named as one of the investors of what became the tmobile arena in las vegas bonderman is a director of continental airlines inc böwe bell  howell co ducati motorcycles spa credicom asia the national education corp beringer wine estates carr realty co virgin cinemas ltd costar group inc gemalto nv ryanair holdings inc and ryanair ltd he has been the chairman of ryanair holdings and ryanair limited since december  he is on the boards of the wilderness society the grand canyon trust the world wildlife fund the university of washington foundation and the american himalayan foundation he previously served on the boards of washington mutual inc american savings bank denbury resources inc and burger king holdings inc he was a board member of uber until he resigned from that position in june  on june   bonderman resigned from the uber board amidst controversy surrounding a sexist response to fellow board member arianna huffington during a company allhands meeting there’s a lot of data that shows when there’s one woman on the board it’s much more likely that there will be a second woman on the board said huffington bonderman replied actually what it shows is that its much more likely to be more talking the uber meeting was among other things slated to discuss efforts to reign in a toxic and sexist culture at the company personal lifeedit bonderman is married to dr laurie michaels they have five children and live in fort worth texas in  for his th birthday bonderman had the rolling stones and john mellencamp play at his birthday party at the joint at hard rock hotel and casino in las vegas john mellencamp played for an hour the rolling stones played for an hour and a half and comedian robin williams entertained guests between acts the party cost  million making it one of the most expensive private concerts ever held in  for his th birthday party bonderman held a private concert by former beatle paul mccartney at wynn las vegas for  guests robin williams also performed a comedy routine bonderman donated  to each guests charity of choice referencesedit  a b forbes the worlds billionaires  david bonderman june    taub orna tpg sells shares of indian company – winwin for everybody jewish business news march    bryant adam november   deal maker takes aim at skies new york times retrieved november     a b c d executive profile  david bonderman jd bloombergcom retrieved june     a b steffy loren march   bonderman rides to rescue of corporate wrecks the journal news white plains new york bloomberg news retrieved june   – via newspaperscom   kantowski ron september   report harrah’s out as proposed arena partner las vegas sun   the management team biographies ryanaircom archived from the original on june   retrieved june   – via wayback machine   uber confirms that it raised m from google ventures and tpg techcrunch august   retrieved april     uber dir